"title": "5719: mothers, responsibilities of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5719",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The fundamental importance of motherhood is recognised throughout Scripture.</p>\n<h2>Motherhood and childbirth</h2>\n<h3>God plans happiness for women in motherhood</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps113:9\">PSA 113:9</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The need for a mother's cleansing after childbirth</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:1-Lev12:8\">LEV 12:1–12:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:22-Luke2:24\">LUK 2:22–2:24</a></p>\n<h2>A mother's relationship with her children</h2>\n<h3>A mother loves and cares for her children</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:7\">1TH 2:7</a></strong> <em>Paul's statement assumes that a mother's normal attitude towards her child is one of love and care.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:48\">LUK 2:48</a></p>\n<h3>A mother's role as teacher</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:8\">PRO 1:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:20\">PRO 6:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:5\">2TI 1:5</a></p>\n<h3>The responsibility to discipline children</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:15\">PRO 29:15</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The joy or sorrow of parents at their children's conduct</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:1\">PRO 10:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:25\">PRO 23:25</a></p>\n<h2>The negative influence of some mothers upon their children</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr22:3\">2CH 22:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:5-Gen27:17\">GEN 27:5–27:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:52\">1KI 22:52</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:6-Matt14:8\">MAT 14:6–14:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:20-Matt20:22\">MAT 20:20–20:22</a></p>\n<h2>Children's reponsibility to honour their parents</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:12\">EXO 20:12</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:16\">DEU 5:16</a> <em>“Honour” implies respect, obedience and care for the parents' needs.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:3\">LEV 19:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:19\">MAT 19:19</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:19\">MRK 10:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:20\">LUK 18:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:1-Eph6:3\">EPH 6:1–6:3</a></p>\n<h3>This honour is due especially to mothers in old age</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:22\">PRO 23:22</a></p>\n<h2>Penalties for disobeying parents</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:15\">EXO 21:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:17\">EXO 21:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:18-Deut21:21\">DEU 21:18–21:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:20\">PRO 20:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:4-Matt15:6\">MAT 15:4–15:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:10-Mark7:13\">MRK 7:10–7:13</a></p>\n<h2>Sexual relations with one's mother or mother-in-law are forbidden</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:7\">LEV 18:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:23\">DEU 27:23</a></p>\n<h2>Upon marriage the mother-child relationship becomes secondary</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:24\">GEN 2:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:5\">MAT 19:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:7\">MRK 10:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:31\">EPH 5:31</a></p>\n<h2>Care for a mother-in-law</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:11\">RUT 2:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:14-Matt8:15\">MAT 8:14–8:15</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:29-Mark1:31\">MRK 1:29–1:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:38\">LUK 4:38</a></p>\n<h2>The ministry of Jesus Christ may produce conflict within families</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:53\">LUK 12:53</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:35-Matt10:36\">MAT 10:35–10:36</a></p>\n<h2>Following Jesus Christ involves a commitment to him even deeper than love of one's parents</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:37\">MAT 10:37</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:26\">LUK 14:26</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ regards those who do God's will as his own family</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:49-Matt12:50\">MAT 12:49–12:50</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:31-Mark3:35\">MRK 3:31–3:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:19-Luke8:21\">LUK 8:19–8:21</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:29\">MAT 19:29</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:29\">MRK 10:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:29-Luke18:30\">LUK 18:29–18:30</a></p>",
